the command
docker run -d --name mysql-container -p 3307:3306 `
  -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root123 `
  -e MYSQL_DATABASE=collage `
  -e MYSQL_USER=admin `
  -e MYSQL_PASSWORD=admin123 `
  mysql:8.0


description of the command 

- docker run -d → Runs the container in detached mode (in the background).
- --name mysql-container → Assigns the container a custom name (mysql-container) so you can reference it easily.
- -p 3307:3306 → Maps host port 3307 to container port 3306.
- This lets you connect to MySQL on your computer using localhost:3307, while inside the container MySQL still listens on its default port 3306.
- -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root123 → Sets the root user password to root123.
- -e MYSQL_DATABASE=collage → Creates a new database named collage automatically when the container starts.
- -e MYSQL_USER=admin → Creates a new MySQL user named admin.
- -e MYSQL_PASSWORD=admin123 → Sets the password for the admin user to admin123.
- mysql:8.0 → Specifies the image to use: the official MySQL image, version 8.0.







